def analyze_sentiment(text):
    if not isinstance(text, str):
        text = ' '.join(text) if isinstance(text, list) else str(text)
        
    blob = TextBlob(text)
    sentiment_score = blob.sentiment.polarity  
    return sentiment_score

y = reviews['sentiment_score'] = reviews['content'].apply(analyze_sentiment)


sns.histplot(reviews['sentiment_score'], kde=True)
plt.xlabel('Sentiment Score')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.title('Distribution of Sentiment Scores in Reviews')
plt.show()

def plot_star_ratings(reviews):
    sns.countplot(x='stars', data=reviews)

    plt.xlabel('Star Ratings')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.show()

def plot_word_cloud(text):
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=600, height=250, background_color='white').generate(text)
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

Preprocessing

In [ ]:
def preprocess_text(text):

    if isinstance(text, list):
        text = ' '.join(text)
        
    text = text.lower()
    text = ''.join([char for char in text if char not in string.punctuation])
    tokens = word_tokenize(text)
    stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
    tokens = [word for word in tokens if word not in stop_words]
    lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
    tokens = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in tokens]
    return ' '.join(tokens)

Cosine Similarity

In [ ]:
def calculate_cosine_similarity(user_input_vector, X):
    similarity_scores = cosine_similarity(user_input_vector, X)
    return similarity_scores[0]

def recommend_destinations(user_input, reviews, top_n=5):
    user_input_text = preprocess_text(user_input)
    user_input_vector = tfidf_vectorizer.transform([user_input_text])
    similarity_scores = calculate_cosine_similarity(user_input_vector, X)

    reviews['similarity_score'] = similarity_scores

    data_sorted = reviews.sort_values(by='similarity_score', ascending=False)

    return data_sorted.head(top_n)

user_input = "I enjoy beach activities and tropical climates"

recommended_destinations = recommend_destinations(user_input, reviews, top_n=5)
print("Top 5 recommended destinations:")
print(recommended_destinations[['hotel', 'content', 'similarity_score', 'stars']])

Create and Run the Chatbot

In [ ]:
import tkinter as tk
from nltk.chat.util import Chat, reflections
pairs = [

    [
        r"(.*)(beach|water sports|tropical|ocean)(.*)",
        ["You seem to enjoy beach activities and tropical climates. How about visiting Boracay?",
         "You might enjoy Punta Cana for its beautiful beaches and water sports."]
    ],
    [
        r"(.*)(skiing|mountains|snow|snowboarding)(.*)",
        ["It sounds like you enjoy winter sports and mountain getaways. How about Whistler or Aspen?",
         "You might like Whistler for skiing or Gran Canaria for a snowy retreat."]
    ],
    [
        r"(hi|hello|hey|greetings|hi there)(.*)",
        ["Hello! How can I help you today?",
         "Hi there! What kind of travel recommendations can I provide you?"]
    ],
   
    [
        r"(.*)(history|culture|museums|monuments)(.*)",
        ["It sounds like you enjoy exploring history and culture. How about visiting Vienna?",
         "You might enjoy Budapest for its rich history and beautiful architecture."]
    ],
    [
        r"(.*)(adventure|hiking|outdoor)(.*)",
        ["You seem to enjoy outdoor adventures. How about visiting Aspen for hiking and exploring?",
         "Whistler might offer you exciting adventures and outdoor activities."]
    ],
    [
        r"(.*)(food|cuisine|restaurants|dining)(.*)",
        ["It seems like you're interested in trying different cuisines. How about visiting Playa del Carmen for its Mexican food?",
         "Gran Canaria offers a mix of local and international cuisines to try."]
    ],
    [
        r"(.*)(family|kids|children|family-friendly)(.*)",
        ["You might enjoy destinations with family-friendly activities. How about visiting Playa del Carmen for its family-friendly resorts?",
         "Gran Canaria offers various family-friendly activities and resorts for all ages."]
    ],
    [
        r"(.*)(nightlife|clubs|parties)(.*)",
        ["If you're looking for exciting nightlife, consider visiting Punta Cana for its clubs and parties.",
         "Boracay offers vibrant nightlife with its beach parties and clubs."]
    ],
    
    [
        r"(.*)",
        ["I'm not sure how to help with that. Could you please provide more details about what you're looking for?",
         "Sorry, I didn't understand that. Can you please rephrase your question?"]
    ],
]


root = tk.Tk()
root.title("Travel Chatbot")

# Define colors and fonts
background_color = "#B2D3C2"
text_color = "#333333"
input_color = "#ffffff"
button_color = "#00FF00"
font_style = "Helvetica"
font_size = 12
button_font_size = 14


# Chat window
text_frame = tk.Frame(root, bg=background_color)
scrollbar = tk.Scrollbar(text_frame)
scrollbar.pack(side=tk.RIGHT, fill=tk.Y)
text_box = tk.Text(text_frame, height=15, width=50, yscrollcommand=scrollbar.set, bg=background_color, fg=text_color, font=(font_style, font_size), state='disabled')
text_box.pack(side=tk.LEFT, fill=tk.BOTH, expand=True)
scrollbar.config(command=text_box.yview)
text_frame.pack(fill=tk.BOTH, expand=True, padx=10, pady=10)

# Message entry box
entry_box = tk.Entry(root, width=40, bg=input_color, fg=text_color, font=(font_style, font_size))
entry_box.pack(padx=10, pady=10)

chat_instance = Chat(pairs, reflections)

# Function to handle sending messages
def ask_from_bot():
    user_input = entry_box.get()
    if user_input:
        text_box.config(state='normal')
        text_box.insert(tk.END, "You: " + user_input + "\n")
        response = chat_instance.respond(user_input)
        text_box.insert(tk.END, "Bot: " + response + "\n")
        text_box.config(state='disabled')
        entry_box.delete(0, tk.END)
    text_box.see(tk.END)

# Send button
send_button = tk.Button(root, text="Send", command=ask_from_bot, bg=button_color, fg="white", font=(font_style, button_font_size))
send_button.pack(pady=5)

# Start the GUI
root.mainloop()
